This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new incremental learning method for large-scale data classification. It also involves the use of decision trees and random forests, which are common techniques in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as image classification is a common application of large-scale data classification. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning is a subfield of AI. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the computational burden of traditional methods and proposes a new method to reduce computational time. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of out-of-bag estimation and out-of-bag boosting to balance accuracy and computational efficiency, which are common techniques in information retrieval.
